================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY CREDITS & ATTRIBUTIONS
================================================================================

This software utilizes several third-party libraries and tools, credited below:

1. FFmpeg
   - Website: https://ffmpeg.org/
   - License: LGPL version 2.1 or later (or GPL version 2 or later, depending on configuration).
   - Description: A complete, cross-platform solution to record, convert, and stream audio and video. FFmpeg builds provided by gyan.dev.

2. Python
   - Website: https://www.python.org/
   - License: PSF License Agreement.
   - Description: The underlying programming language powering this application's backend and command-line interfaces.

3. Flask
   - Website: https://palletsprojects.com/p/flask/
   - License: BSD 3-Clause License.
   - Description: Lightweight WSGI web application framework used to build and serve the Web UI dashboard.

4. Rich
   - Website: https://github.com/Textualize/rich
   - License: MIT License.
   - Description: Python library for writing rich text (with color and style) to the terminal, and for displaying beautiful tables, progress bars, and banners in the CLI.

5. Psutil
   - Website: https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil
   - License: BSD 3-Clause License.
   - Description: Cross-platform library for retrieving information on running processes and system utilization. Used for secure conversion process cancellation and subprocess tree management.
